usage: scaffold_tenant.py [-h] [--tenant TENANT] [--db DB] [-o OUTPUT_DIR]
                          [--catalog] [--non-interactive]
                          [--namespaces NAMESPACES]
                          [--routing-profile ROUTING_PROFILE]
                          [--topology {1:1,N:1,1:N}]
                          [--mapping-instance MAPPING_INSTANCE]
                          [--mapping-filter MAPPING_FILTER]
                          [--silent-mode {warning,critical,all,disable}]
                          [--severity-dedup {enable,disable}]
                          [--routing-receiver ROUTING_RECEIVER]
                          [--routing-receiver-type {webhook,email,slack,teams,rocketchat,pagerduty}]
                          [--routing-smarthost ROUTING_SMARTHOST]
                          [--routing-group-by ROUTING_GROUP_BY]
                          [--routing-group-wait ROUTING_GROUP_WAIT]
                          [--routing-group-interval ROUTING_GROUP_INTERVAL]
                          [--routing-repeat-interval ROUTING_REPEAT_INTERVAL]
                          [--profile PROFILE] [--from-onboard FROM_ONBOARD]
                          [--generate-profile GENERATE_PROFILE]
                          [--tier {prod,staging}]

Interactive tenant config generator for Dynamic Alerting

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --tenant TENANT       Tenant namespace name (e.g., db-c)
  --db DB               Comma-separated DB types
                        (mariadb,redis,mongodb,elasticsearch)
  -o OUTPUT_DIR, --output-dir OUTPUT_DIR
                        Output directory (default: scaffold_output)
  --catalog             Display list of supported exporters
  --non-interactive     Skip interactive prompts (requires --tenant and --db)
  --namespaces NAMESPACES
                        Comma-separated K8s namespace names for N:1 tenant
                        mapping (e.g., ns1,ns2,ns3)
  --routing-profile ROUTING_PROFILE
                        Routing profile name (ADR-007), e.g., team-sre-apac.
                        When set, tenant YAML will include _routing_profile
                        reference
  --topology {1:1,N:1,1:N}
                        Tenant mapping topology (ADR-006): 1:1 (default), N:1
                        (requires --namespaces), 1:N (generates mapping hint)
  --mapping-instance MAPPING_INSTANCE
                        Source instance name for 1:N topology (e.g., oracle-
                        prod-01)
  --mapping-filter MAPPING_FILTER
                        PromQL filter for 1:N topology (e.g.,
                        schema=~"app_a_.*")
  --silent-mode {warning,critical,all,disable}
                        Silent mode: alerts fire (TSDB records) but
                        notifications suppressed
  --severity-dedup {enable,disable}
                        Severity dedup: suppress warning notification when
                        critical fires (default: enable)
  --routing-receiver ROUTING_RECEIVER
                        Alert routing receiver address (URL or email list
                        depending on type)
  --routing-receiver-type {webhook,email,slack,teams,rocketchat,pagerduty}
                        Receiver type (default: webhook)
  --routing-smarthost ROUTING_SMARTHOST
                        SMTP smarthost for email receiver (e.g.,
                        smtp.example.com:587)
  --routing-group-by ROUTING_GROUP_BY
                        Comma-separated group_by labels (e.g.,
                        alertname,severity)
  --routing-group-wait ROUTING_GROUP_WAIT
                        Group wait duration (e.g., 30s, range: 5s-5m)
  --routing-group-interval ROUTING_GROUP_INTERVAL
                        Group interval duration (e.g., 5m, range: 5s-5m)
  --routing-repeat-interval ROUTING_REPEAT_INTERVAL
                        Repeat interval duration (e.g., 4h, range: 1m-72h)
  --profile PROFILE     Tenant profile name (e.g., standard-mariadb-prod).
                        When set, tenant YAML will reference the named profile
                        and only contain explicit overrides.
  --from-onboard FROM_ONBOARD
                        Path to onboard-hints.json (auto-scaffold from onboard
                        results)
  --generate-profile GENERATE_PROFILE
                        Generate a _profiles.yaml skeleton. Value is profile
                        name (e.g., standard-mariadb-prod). Requires --db.
  --tier {prod,staging}
                        Environment tier for profile thresholds

Examples:
  scaffold_tenant.py                                                      # Interactive mode
  scaffold_tenant.py --catalog                                            # Display supported exporters
  scaffold_tenant.py --tenant db-c --db mariadb,redis                     # Non-interactive mode
  scaffold_tenant.py --tenant db-c --db mariadb -o out/                   # Specify output directory
  scaffold_tenant.py --tenant db-c --db mariadb --namespaces ns1,ns2,ns3  # With N:1 tenant mapping
